Pseudo-residual analysis with perfect data

Xavier Didelot

2025-09-04

We start by generating a dated tree with no structure and a small effective population size \(N_e g=1\) year relative to the sampling frame of 10 years between 2010 and 2020:

library(DiagnoDating,quietly=T)
set.seed(3)
dates=runif(100,2010,2020)
dt=simcoaltree(dates,alpha=1)
plot(dt,show.tip.label = F)
axisPhylo(backward = F)

Next we generate a phylogenetic tree using a Poisson(10) mutation model:

tree=simobsphy(dt,mu=10,model='poisson')
plot(tree,show.tip.label = F)
axisPhylo(1,backward=F)

A root-to-tip regression analysis works perfectly:

res=roottotip(tree,dates,rate=10,permTest = 0)

Make up analysis with true parameters:

r=resDating(dt,tree,algo='TRUTH',model = 'poisson',rate=10)
print(r)
## Result from TRUTH, model poisson, clock rate 10.00, relaxation parameter 0.00, root date 2008.06

Pseudo-residual analysis:

plotLikBranches(r)

plotResid(r)

print(testResid(r))
## 
##  Anderson-Darling test of goodness-of-fit
##  Null hypothesis: Normal distribution
##  with parameters mean = 0.000, sd = 1.000
## 
## data:  n
## An = 1.4827, p-value = 0.1807
